=\"elementor-tab-title-2012\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p>Drugstore Beetles are small insects that measure between 2.5 to 3.5 mm in length.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-tab-title elementor-tab-mobile-title\" aria-selected=\"false\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tab\" tabindex=\"-1\" aria-controls=\"elementor-tab-content-2013\" aria-expanded=\"false\">Description<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div id=\"elementor-tab-content-2013\" class=\"elementor-tab-content elementor-clearfix\" data-tab=\"3\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"elementor-tab-title-2013\" tabindex=\"0\" hidden=\"hidden\"><p>The body structure of drugstore beetles is characterized by their oval-shaped bodies. Their bodies have a distinct humpbacked appearance and are covered in tiny hairs. The head of the drugstore beetle is elongated with large antennae protruding from it. Their mouthparts are designed for chewing and they use them to break down everything from wood to dried fruits and vegetables. These beetles also have six legs that enable them to crawl across surfaces, allowing them to move from one food source to another.<\/p><\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-6031098\" data-id=\"6031098\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-14a78f6\" data-id=\"14a78f6\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-22c17aa elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"22c17aa\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"headin