ntor-g-recaptcha\" data-sitekey=\"6LdtFHIhAAAAAENXS8JO7-KljjwNvLYnJjJRb5gX\" data-type=\"v3\" data-action=\"Form\" data-badge=\"inline\" data-size=\"invisible\"><\/div><\/div>\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-field-group elementor-column elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5a5eb01 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5a5eb01\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-6295e1d\" data-id=\"6295e1d\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-9d2d2d4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"9d2d2d4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">What are drugstore beetles?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-4cbbed6 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"4cbbed6\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Drugstore beetles, also known as biscuit beetles or bread beetles, are small brown insects that feed on dry food products. They are commonly found in households and commercial food storage facilities all over the world. The adult beetle is oval-shaped and measures about 2-3mm in length. They have six legs and two antennae that act as sensors to help them navigate.<\/p><p>Despite their name, drugstore beetles don&#8217;t just infest drugstores but can be found in a variety of pantry items such as flour, cereal, spices, dried fruits and nuts, pet food and even leather goods. Once they find their way into a food source they lay eggs which hatch into larvae that burrow into the product causing extensive damage. Infestations can occur quickly and can be difficult to control once established.<\/p><p>Protect your home from the intrusion of drugstore beetles,\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/oriental-cockroaches\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><u>Oriental cockroaches<\/u><\/b><\/a>,\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/crane-flies\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><u>crane flies<\/u><\/b><\/a>, and\u00a0<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/grain-beetles\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><b><u>grain beetles<\/u><\/b><\/a>\u00a0with our expert advice on comprehensive pest control for a peaceful living environment<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-b3a296c elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"b3a296c\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Habitat, Diet and Lifecycle of Drugstore Beetles<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c9c8766 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"c9c8766\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Drugstore beetles are a type of pest that can be found in various parts of the world, including Canada. They are known for their ability to infest and damage a wide range of items, including food products, fabrics, and other organic materials. We will explore the habitat, diet, and lifecycle of drugstore beetles in Canada.<\/p><p><strong>Habitat: <\/strong>Drugstore beetles can be found in a variety of habitats in Canada, including homes, grocery stores, warehouses, and other areas where organic materials are present. They prefer warm and humid conditions and are often found in areas with high humidity levels, such as kitchens, bathrooms, and basements. They are known to infest a wide range of items, including flour, cereal, spices, pet food, and even prescription drugs.<\/p><p><strong>Diet: <\/strong>Drugstore beetles feed on a wide range of organic materials, including grains, seeds, nuts, and other dry goods. They are also known to infest animal products, such as dried meat, feathers, and wool. In homes, they can be found in kitchen pantries and cabinets, where they feed on stored food products.<\/p><p><strong>Lifecycle: <\/strong>The lifecycle of drugstore beetles begins when adult females lay their eggs on or near a food source. The larvae hatch from the eggs and begin to feed on the food source. The larvae go through several stages of development before pupating and transforming into adults. The entire lifecycle can take anywhere from two months to several years, depending on environmental conditions such as temperature and humidity.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-3e2eb48 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"3e2eb48\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">How do drugstore beetles get into homes?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-a8ce72b elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"a8ce72b\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Drugstore beetles are a common pest in households and they get their name from their tendency to infest food items found in drugstores. These pests can easily find their way into our homes without us even knowing it. The main reason why drugstore beetles invade homes is that they are attracted to food sources such as grains, cereals, spices, and flour.<\/p><p>Drugstore beetles can enter your home through various means including cracks and gaps in the walls or foundation of your house. They may also hitchhike on infested products like grains or pet food which you bring home from the grocery store unknowingly. Additionally, these pests have a strong sense of smell and can detect the presence of any potential food source within 20-30 feet.<\/p><p>Once inside your home, drugstore beetles reproduce quickly and lay eggs on surfaces near the source of food such as cabinets or pantry shelves. Infestation by drugstore beetles is not only limited to residential dwellings but also occurs in warehouses, processing plants or grain storage facilities where there is an abundance of stored foods which provide ideal conditions for growth and propagation of these pests. Therefore, proper sanitation practices coupled with regular inspection can help prevent an infestation by drugstore beetles at homes or commercial premises alike.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-2e601fe elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-s