_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Drugstore beetles are a common pest that can infest pantry staples such as flour, spices, and cereals. If left unchecked, they can cause extensive damage to stored goods and pose health risks to homeowners. To protect against these pests, there are several measures homeowners can take.<\/p><p>Firstly, ensure that all food items are stored in sealed containers made of glass or hard plastic. These materials reduce the risk of infestation by making it difficult for the beetle larvae to penetrate the container walls. Secondly, check all incoming food purchases for signs of contamination before storing them in your pantry. Discard any packages with damaged seals or holes as these may have already been infiltrated by drugstore beetles.<\/p><p>Finally, maintain good hygiene practices in your kitchen and pantry areas. Regularly clean out cupboards and pantries to remove any potential breeding sites for drugstore beetles. Any spills or crumbs should be cleaned up immediately to prevent attracting pests into your home. By implementing these simple measures on a regular basis, you can effectively protect your home from an infestation of drugstore beetles and keep your pantry safe from harm.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-d78dd4d elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"d78dd4d\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-c7c5256\" data-id=\"c7c5256\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t